said that we would get done for

00:10:35.610 --> 00:10:37.370
today, I want it done.

00:10:38.580 --> 00:10:43.729
So it's not enough to wave hands and
say voila, this works.

00:10:45.100 --> 00:10:47.009
&gt;&gt; I signed up to succeed
in the Grand Challenge.

00:10:48.169 --> 00:10:53.879
This time around, the red team
will be more like a red army.

00:10:53.879 --> 00:10:55.299
It is a machine to reckoned with.

00:10:56.950 --> 00:11:01.350
&gt;&gt; Red Whittaker's resume is
a veritable history of field robotics.

00:11:01.350 --> 00:11:05.379
His robots are battle-hardened machines
built to clean up Three Mile Island and

00:11:05.379 --> 00:11:06.519
then Chernobyl.

00:11:06.519 --> 00:11:11.000
These rust belt brutes can map
dangerous mines, load trucks,

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:14.000
remove asbestos and mow hay.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:18.441
They're global explorers that have
ventured across volcanoes, deserts and

00:11:18.441 --> 00:11:19.120
glaciers.

00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:25.211
[MUSIC]

00:11:25.211 --> 00:11:29.048
Now, Whittaker has staked his reputation
on winning the Grand Challenge.

00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:34.480
To double his chances, he's planning
to run two robots in the next race.

00:11:35.679 --> 00:11:39.719
In addition to their veteran Sandstorm,
the red team will transform this new

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:43.240
Hummer into a more aggressive
machine called Highlander.

00:11:45.750 --> 00:11:46.700
For more than a year,

00:11:46.700 --> 00:11:50.319
Wait Gibbs has been documenting
Whittaker's Grand Challenge quest.

00:11:51.669 --> 00:11:55.979
&gt;&gt; Red Whittaker is nothing if
not an ambitious man [LAUGH].

00:11:55.980 --> 00:12:00.159
&gt;&gt; He's a roboticist who in his weekends
goes out and drives a tractor for

00:12:00.159 --> 00:12:02.009
ten hours on his farm.

00:12:02.009 --> 00:12:06.129
And who likes to actually get in and
get his hands greasy and

00:12:06.129 --> 00:12:08.039
dirty inside an engine.

