To replace the human behind the wheel,
team members have

00:13:01.139 --> 00:13:05.370
installed an electromechanical system
to steer, shift, throttle and brake.

00:13:07.230 --> 00:13:11.239
They're installing sensors so
Highlander can see and GPS receivers so

00:13:11.239 --> 00:13:12.984
it can follow the race course.

00:13:12.984 --> 00:13:15.668
[MUSIC]

00:13:15.668 --> 00:13:18.144
And they're giving the robot a brain.

00:13:18.144 --> 00:13:22.530
Filling it with software,
so it can drive by itself.

00:13:22.530 --> 00:13:24.849
Now it might seem easy for
robots to drive.

00:13:27.340 --> 00:13:29.160
It happens all the time in movies.

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:33.254
&gt;&gt; I'll drive.

00:13:33.254 --> 00:13:34.629
&gt;&gt; You think of the Terminator movies.

00:13:34.629 --> 00:13:38.163
Science fiction gives a really distorted
view of capabilities of robots.

00:13:40.419 --> 00:13:44.339
Those robots are able to
identify specific individuals.

00:13:44.340 --> 00:13:47.629
But in reality, robots have very
limited senses of perception.

00:13:49.360 --> 00:13:51.830
&gt;&gt; Robots know nothing
about their environment and

00:13:51.830 --> 00:13:53.650
they can't think like humans.

00:13:53.649 --> 00:13:56.699
But they're really good
at crunching numbers.

00:13:56.700 --> 00:14:00.242
Most rely on laser range
finders to perceive the world.

00:14:00.241 --> 00:14:03.283
[MUSIC]

00:14:03.283 --> 00:14:06.748
Inside a beam of light bounces
off a spinning mirror and

00:14:06.748 --> 00:14:08.490
sweeps the terrain ahead.

00:14:09.820 --> 00:14:12.940
By measuring the time it takes
the beam to hit something and

00:14:12.940 --> 00:14:16.780
return, the range finder can measure
its distance from the vehicle.

00:14:17.950 --> 00:14:21.200
Scanners are mounted in pairs
to measure different things.

00:14:22.980 --> 00:14:27.470
Some look for smooth road ahead, others
look for the road edge on each side.

00:14:28.909 --> 00:14:33.620
Some look for vertical objects, a rock
or a fence post that can kill a robot.

00:14:36.330 --> 00:14:40.410
Putting it all together, this becomes
Highlander's view of the world.

00:14:40.409 --> 00:14:44.934
&gt;&gt; A road map made from millions
of numbers that basically tells

00:14:44.934 --> 00:14:46.983
the robot bumpy or smooth.

00:14:46.984 --> 00:14:52.042
[MUSIC]

00:14:52.042 --> 00:14:56.776
Off on its own, Highlander will try to
avoid obstacles for the first time.

00:14:56.775 --> 00:15:06.775
[MUSIC]

00:15:11.070 --> 00:15:15.150
Improving its driving skills will
take endless hours of programming.

00:15:17.519 --> 00:15:22.840
&gt;&gt; The red team robots have on the order
of a million lines of computer code.

00:15:22.840 --> 00:15:26.840
Even so, they do very simple
reasoning about the world.

00:15:26.840 --> 00:15:28.700
They look for flat spots.

00:15:28.700 --> 00:15:31.180
Flat is good, drive on flat spots.

00:15:31.179 --> 00:15:32.899
Anything that's not flat, avoid it.

00:15:34.590 --> 00:15:38.271
&gt;&gt; But for the red team winning
the Grand Challenge involves much more

00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:39.921
than writing computer code.

